1) Compact prompt — paste this if you want a quick, high-quality output
SYSTEM: You are a senior software architect and product designer for enterprise ERP systems. Produce clean, developer-ready design docs, DDLs, REST API contracts, screen mockups (ASCII), workflows, testing checklists and future-enhancement items.

USER: I will provide:
  1) a short functional requirement summary (plain text), and
  2) an existing database DDL file (SQL) named "<filename>.sql".

Task:
  • Parse the DDL and map tables to logical ERP modules.
  • Propose a canonical list of modules (with short purpose descriptions).
  • For each module produce:
    1. Refactored DDL (full CREATE TABLE statements, indexes, FKs, sample seed data).
    2. A Design Document with 10 sections: Overview, Data Context, Screen Layouts, Data Models, User Workflows, Visual Design, Accessibility, Testing, Deployment/Runbook, Future Enhancements.
    3. Standardized 7-role permission matrix (roles: SuperAdmin, Management, Principal, Teacher, Accountant, Parent, Student — adapt if I supply different roles).
    4. Multiple UI mockups (ASCII diagrams) for Desktop/Tablet/Mobile for the key screens.
    5. REST API contracts: endpoint, method, auth, request/response JSON examples, validations, status codes and error responses, sample curl.
    6. Database table schema context: purpose of table, columns explained, relationships, growth considerations, partition/index suggestions.
    7. Step-by-step user workflow instructions (happy path + common alternate/error flows).
    8. Detailed testing checklist (unit, integration, E2E, security, accessibility, performance) with example test-cases.
    9. Future enhancement ideas and migration/upgrade notes.

Formatting & deliverables:
  • Return everything in Markdown with clear headings. Use code blocks for SQL, JSON and cURL.
  • Provide the refactored DDL as a single downloadable SQL file (present as a code block named "<module>_ddl.sql").
  • For each REST contract provide request/response JSON examples and at least one full cURL example.
  • Provide 2–3 ASCII mockups per key screen (desktop/tablet/mobile).
  • Keep each module section self-contained so I can copy/paste into files.

Now parse the attached DDL file "<filename>.sql" and my requirements (below). Produce the full result as described.

